Verification notes
------------------
The rebased patches in this folder were tested by:
  * 18, 19, 13: copy-from-2.12 — paths target pinned-commit ZRTPCPP
    source, no rebase needed.
  * 15: applied against a stub vpx.c with line-503 context (matches
    2.17 structure). Hunk landed cleanly.
  * 20: applied against a stub Makefile reproducing vanilla 2.17's
    PJMEDIA_OBJS line layout. Two new file additions are byte-for-byte
    drops; Makefile hunk fuzz=2 against the stub (will be exact
    against real 2.17).
  * 27: applied against a saved 2.17 transport.h + the sylk_aead
    file from patch 20. transport.h hunk landed at line 775 with
    offset 3.
  * 24: applied against the real 2.17 endpoint.c. Hunk landed at
    line 883 with offset 1.
  * 07: applied against a stub opus.c reproducing the 2.17
    factory_enum_codecs context. Landed at line 552 with offset -2.
  * 25: applied against a structurally-equivalent libswscale file.
    Two hunks landed.
  * 11: NOT yet verified end-to-end. The header-hunk context lines
    around pjmedia_ice_cb and pjmedia_ice_get_grp_lock match the
    fetched 2.17 transport_ice.h. The .c hunk line numbers are
    approximate (the function bodies were past the fetched range).
    Run get_dependencies.sh against a real 2.17 tarball to verify.

When applying the full series against a fresh 2.17 expand:
  cd deps && wget https://github.com/pjsip/pjproject/archive/2.17.tar.gz
  cd .. && PJSIP_VERSION=2.17 ./get_dependencies.sh
expect each "Applying patch ..." line to be followed by zero "FAILED"
or "rejects" messages. Hunks succeeding with offsets / fuzz are fine;
hunks REJECTED need a manual look.
